Package de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.measurement.order

Types used to communicate measurement orders and results from and to MeasurementTools.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    LaunchConfiguration
    Interface for classes that execute the code under test.
    MeasurementEvent
    An event occurring while measuring software.
    MeasurementEventVisitor
    A visitor for MeasurementEvents useful to iterate over a sequence of different such events.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractMeasurementEvent
    An abstract MeasurementEvent, already having a code section.
    CodeSectionEnteredEvent
    An event for the fact that a code section was being started to be executed.
    CodeSectionLeftEvent
    An event for the fact that a code section was being left to be executed.
    EclipseLaunchConfigurationLaunchConfiguration
    A launch configuration that starts in its EclipseLaunchConfigurationLaunchConfiguration.execute() method an eclipse launch configuration.
    MeasurementOrder
    The measurement order specifies what to measure for a MeasurementTool.
    ParameterCharacteriser
    Characterises an arbitrary parameter as real;
    ParameterValueCapturedEvent
    Note: Designing this class is out of the project’s first iteration’s scope.
    ResourceDemandCapturedEvent
    An event for the fact that the amount of a certain resource a certain code section demands was captured.
